        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Had a house network set up with media centers playing movies over the LAN, everything was working great. One day it just stopped working; no TVs could play movies from any SMB shares. After days of back and forth it turned out that Windows Live Sync, if installed on any connected machine, messes up SMB shares on the entire network by introducing a new authentication method not supported on older devices.<br /><br />The bug was in the media devices not correctly handling this rarely used SMB feature, but the net effect was really weird.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
