          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              A while back, I was selling LANs, back in the coax-cables days ('90s). One of my clients kept having LAN issues after going back from lunch. They investigated and castigated the cleaners, people in the break room, the fridge, the microwave, the network card... no luck.<br /><br />We finally got called in to fix it, or else. Turns out, early afternoon was the only time the sun got through the window of a small backroom, struck the cable directly, which made the outer plastic dilate just a bit... and since there was a micro-fracture of the conductor inside, that was enough to make the cable fail.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
