              The strangest fault I had recently was with a classroom &quot;all in one&quot; PC at work, basically a standard desktop pc with speakers in the base and a monitor bolted onto it. A teacher reported that it was making a horrible screeching noise. Get up there and lo and behold, it was. The really strange thing was that I found that I could vary the pitch of the screech and even stop it entirely by waving my hands in front of or touching different parts of the computer, just like a theremin. <br /><br />Turns out there is a microphone embedded in the top of the monitor that was playing up. Unplugging it shut the thing up <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/smile.png" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
