              I had a first generation MacBook Pro. Thing worked very well, especially considering it was Apple's first attempt at making a consumer Intel-based computer - but the machine would occasionally go 'moo'.<br /><br />Yes, 'moo' - like a cow. It was like living near a dairy farm. Moo.<br /><br />(Evidence that I'm not completely crazy <a href="http://www.moofix.com/index.php" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">here</a>. The issue went away with a subsequent firmware update...)<br /><br />Mooooo.

              

              
              
